Coffee Survey Filtered Data

Source: R/dataset.R
coffee_filtered.Rd

The coffee_filtered dataset contains survey data on coffee consumption patterns, including information on respondents' demographics and coffee preferences.

Usage

coffee_filtered

Format

A data frame with n rows and the following columns:

id

Unique identifier for each respondent (integer).

age

Age group of the respondent as a factor with levels: <18 years old, 18-24 years old, 25-34 years old, 35-44 years old, 45-54 years old, 55-64 years old, >65 years old.

cups

Number of cups of coffee consumed per day (numeric).

brew

Preferred brew method of the respondent (character), e.g., "Espresso", "Drip".

gender

Gender of the respondent (character), with levels "Male" and "Female".

purchase

Type of coffee purchase method (character), such as "in-store" or "online".

total_spend

Total amount spent on coffee in a month (numeric), in USD.

spent_equipment

Amount spent on coffee brewing equipment (numeric), in USD.

favorite

Favorite type of coffee as specified by the respondent (character), e.g., "Latte", "Cappuccino".

Source

The data was collected from a coffee consumption survey.

Details

This dataset can be used to analyze trends in coffee consumption based on variables such as age group, gender, preferred coffee type, and other relevant factors.
